import React from "react";
import { ServicesCard,Ser } from "./ServicesElements";

const Services = () => {
  return (
    <>
      <ServicesContainer id="services">
        <ServicesH1> Our Services</ServicesH1>
        <ServicesWrapper>
          <ServicesCard>
            <ServicesIcon scr={icon} />
            <Servicesh2> Reduce Expenses</Servicesh2>
            <ServicesP>
              Learn how to build a React website using styled components and
              React smooth scroll. The website is fully responsive and we will
              be using React Hooks and React Router for this project
            </ServicesP>
          </ServicesCard>
          <ServicesCard>
            <ServicesIcon scr={icon2} />
            <Servicesh2> Virtual Offices</Servicesh2>
            <ServicesP>
              Learn how to build a React website using styled components and
              React smooth scroll. The website is fully responsive and we will
              be using React Hooks and React Router for this project
            </ServicesP>
          </ServicesCard>
          <ServicesCard>
            <ServicesIcon scr={icon3} />
            <Servicesh2> Premium Benefits</Servicesh2>
            <ServicesP>
              Learn how to build a React website using styled components and
              React smooth scroll. The website is fully responsive and we will
              be using React Hooks and React Router for this project
            </ServicesP>
          </ServicesCard>
        </ServicesWrapper>
      </ServicesContainer>
    </>
  );
};

export default Services;
